-- Henderson Land wins auction for HK$4.7 bln commercial site in Hong Kong
-- 
-- Wed Sep 03, 2014 05:13AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Sept 3 (Reuters) - Hong Kong developer Henderson Land Development won an auction for a commercial site worth HK$4.7 billion ($605 million), the government said on Wednesday.

Smart Bright Development Ltd, unit of Henderson Land, beat 17 bids from other Hong Kong and Chinese developers, including Cheung Kong (Holdings) Ltd <0001.HK>, Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd <0016.HK>, New World Development Company Ltd <0017.HK> and Emperor International Holdings Ltd <0163.HK>, to build office and hotel buildings in the heart of Hong Kong's shopping district of Tsim Sha Tsui. A Reuters poll of three analysts gave a forecast of HK$4.51 billion, HK$3.4 billion and HK$3.4 billion for the site of 0.26 hectares, respectively.